'''''Belong''''' is the second studio album from [[New York City|New York]] [[indie music|indie]] band [[The Pains of Being Pure at Heart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepainsofbeingpureatheart.com |title=The Pains of Being Pure at Heart |publisher=Thepainsofbeingpureatheart.com |date= |accessdate=2011-03-25}}</ref>  It was released on March 29, 2011 through [[Slumberland Records]].  The album was recorded in the fall of 2010 after extensive touring in support of [[The Pains of Being Pure at Heart (album)|the band's debut album]].  It was produced by [[Flood (producer)|Flood]] and mixed by [[Alan Moulder]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pitchfork.com/news/41451-the-pains-of-being-pure-at-heart-talk-new-lp/# |title=The Pains of Being Pure at Heart Talk New LP |publisher=Pitchfork |date= |accessdate=2012-03-12}}</ref>

== Background and recording ==
In an interview with [[Pitchfork Media|Pitchfork]], vocalist/guitarist Kip Berman explained that the band "wanted the songs to exist in an immediate and instinctual place. The album sounds like we're taking away what we were hiding behind before. Lyrically, the first record had a lot of remembered experiences that I was looking back on and trying to make more clever, which can sound contrived. I like the idea of lyrics that don't get beyond themselves but catch you and make an impression. I think that's more emotionally compelling." <ref>{{cite web|url=http://pitchfork.com/news/41451-the-pains-of-being-pure-at-heart-talk-new-lp/# |title=The Pains of Being Pure at Heart Talk New LP |publisher=Pitchfork |date= |accessdate=2012-03-12}}</ref>

