February of 2011 saw the announcement of Belong. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tinymixtapes.com/news/pains-being-pure-heart-announce-details-belong-out-march
|title=Tiny Mix Tapes announce Belong|accessdate=2012-03-13}}</ref>The sophomore LP was proceeded by the release of "Heart in Your Heartbreak"  and "Belong", the title track.

The album's release will be followed by a national tour, supported by [[indie pop]]/[[Electronic music|electronic]] artist [[Twin Shadow]]. On March 10, 2011, The full album was posted on their website for streaming.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepainsofbeingpureatheart.com |title=The Pains of Being Pure at Heart |publisher=Thepainsofbeingpureatheart.com |date= |accessdate=2011-03-25}}</ref>

The album  has been received positively by music critics, earning a 76 on review aggregator site [[Metacritic]], indicating "generally favorable reviews".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/belong/critic-reviews|title=Critic Reviews for Belong at Metacritic|accessdate=2011-03-28}}</ref>

On March 23, 2011, "Heart In Your Heartbreak" was performed on the Late Show with David Letterman<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noisevox.org/node/25572
 |title=The Pains of Being Pure at Heart on Letterman |publisher=Noisevox.org |date= |accessdate=2012-03-13}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=URxhR8Ekq7U
 |title=The Pains of Being Pure at Heart on Letterman |publisher=Youtube.com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-13}}</ref>. Tours across the United States, Europe, and United Kingdom saw the year out for the five-piece. In 2012, the band returned to Australia and New Zealand for the St. Jerome's Laneway Festival in January and February<ref>{{cite web|url=perth.lanewayfestival.com.au
 |title=Laneway Festival homepage |publisher=perth.lanewayfestival.com.au |date= |accessdate=2012-03-13}}</ref>.. After this, Japan, China, and Singapore were visited by the performers.

